cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a protocol for network size estimation over a tree-shaped overlay.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of tree-based protocols in distributed systems.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with network size estimation and subnetworks.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the construction of a continuous time Markov model for analyzing the protocol.
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper studies the performance of the protocol under churn.
